title: Sylian Mokono
text:
Sylian Aldren Mokono (born 22 March 1999) is a Dutch <a href="association%20football">football</a> player of <a href="South%20Africa">South Africa</a>n descent. He plays for <a href="FC%20Utrecht">FC Utrecht</a> and <a href="Jong%20FC%20Utrecht">Jong FC Utrecht</a>.
Club career.
He made his <a href="Eerste%20Divisie">Eerste Divisie</a> debut for <a href="Jong%20FC%20Utrecht">Jong FC Utrecht</a> on 27 August 2018 in a game against <a href="N.E.C.%20%28football%20club%29">NEC</a>, as a 63rd-minute substitute for <a href="Rick%20Mulder">Rick Mulder</a>.
He made his <a href="Eredivisie">Eredivisie</a> debut for <a href="FC%20Utrecht">FC Utrecht</a> on 29 November 2020 in a game against <a href="Feyenoord">Feyenoord</a>.
